        <name xml:lang="en">[thio]carbamate-compound</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This exchange is an aggregate of proxies for applied pesticide(s) Flubendiamide, Indoxacarb, Methomyl, Carbaryl (2.611E-2 kg/ha {1,2,2,1,1}; 3.428E-2 kg/ha {1,2,2,1,1}; 2.64E+0 kg/ha {1,2,2,1,1}; 6.101E-2 kg/ha {1,2,2,1,1}, respectively).
Data reported a quantity of total insecticides/herbicides/fungicides applied in sweet corn is sometimes available even when many of the substances in the category are reported with a “D”. If this total is available, the amount remaining after the sum of substance-specific values is accounted for is divided equally among the substances reported with a “D”. If the sum of available values exceeds or equals the total reported, any remaining “D” substances are treated as zero and omitted. 
From SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021, https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC</comment>
