      <intermediateExchange id="1acdfd4e-c36e-5625-a39c-5a586cc2e51e" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="0.000237914799711192" intermediateExchangeId="7225e2a6-7fd6-40e2-b341-f097b027d119" activityLinkId="c9e6a57e-3ae0-57ed-9914-50f1def85f20">
        <name xml:lang="en">application of plant protection product, by field sprayer</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">4.00 ha/ha (2.38E-4 ha/kg Sweet Corn) application of plant protection product, by sprayer
The dataset has an effective number of passes for application of pesticides of 2.37 ha: 1.03 applications of herbicides on 26.8% of cropped area, 2.15 applications of insecticides on 70.0% of cropped area, 1.10 applications of fungicides on 53.7% of cropped area (USDA NASS 2022d). Application by sprayer accounts for 100% (2.37 passes) WI NASS (2021) Wisconsin Custom Rate Guide 2020. USDA, NASS, Wisconsin Field Office. https://www.nass.usda.gov/Statistics_by_State/Wisconsin/Publications/WI-CRate20.pdf
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance unless otherwise noted.  (UWM Extension 2014, Hanna, Mark 2016, Schuler and Frank 1998, Lattz and Schnitkey 2021b).  Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. 
Source(s): 
WI NASS (2021) Wisconsin Custom Rate Guide 2020. USDA, NASS, Wisconsin Field Office. https://www.nass.usda.gov/Statistics_by_State/Wisconsin/Publications/WI-CRate20.pdf; DeBruin J and Butzen S (2020) Nitrogen uptake by corn . Pioneer. https://www.pioneer.com/us/agronomy/nitrogen_uptake_corn.htmlaccessed 11-20-2021; NAAA (2020) Letter to the South Dakota Public Utilities Commission, July 30, 2020. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://puc.sd.gov/commission/dockets/electric/2021/EL21-018/prefiledexhibits/MBExhH.pdf; NAAA (2019) NAAA Member Survey Report. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://www.agaviation.org/; Wilde M (2010) "Dusting crops a boon, necessity for farmers," in the WFC Courier, August 16, 2010.https://iowadot.gov/aviation/news/pdfs/Dusting%20crops%20a%20boonnecessity%20for%20farmers.pdf; FAA (2019) Table 5.1 - 2019 GENERAL AVIATION AND PART 135 TOTAL FUEL CONSUMED AND AVERAGE FUEL CONSUMPTION RATE BY AIRCRAFT TYPE, Table 3.2 - 2019 GENERAL AVIATION AND PART 135  TOTAL HOURS FLOWN BY ACTUAL USE BY AIRCRAFT TYPE. Federal Aviation Administration. https://www.faa.gov/data_research/aviation_data_statistics/general_aviation/CY2019/; Fritz B (2018) “Best Practices for Aerial Application” in EPA webinar series "Pesticide Spray Drift Series—3 Parts". USDA. https://www.epa.gov/sites/default/files/2019-04/documents/best-practices-for-aerial-application-slides.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021a) Machinery Cost Estimates: Summary. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/machinery-cost-estimates_summary.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021b) Machinery Cost Estimates: Field Operations. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/field_operations.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021c) Machinery Cost Estimates: Harvesting. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/harvest_operations_2021.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021d) Machinery Cost Estimates: Tractors. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/tractor_costs_2021.pdf; Swanson, Schnitkey, Paulson, Zulauf, Coppess (2020a) "Cost Management: Tillage Operations." farmdoc daily (10):151. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdocdaily.illinois.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fdd180820.pdf; Swanson, Schnitkey, Paulson, Zulauf, Coppess (2020b) "Cost Management: Harvest Operations." farmdoc daily (10):158. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdocdaily.illinois.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/fdd010920.pdf; Kanissery et al. (2022) CHAPTER 17. SWEET CORN PRODUCTION. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv135; Liu et al (2022b) CHAPTER 2. FERTILIZER MANAGEMENT FOR VEGETABLE PRODUCTION IN FLORIDA. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv296; IPM (2002) Crop Profile for Corn (Sweet) in Florida. Integrated Pest Management. https://ipmdata.ipmcenters.org/documents/cropprofiles/FLSweetcorn2002.pdf;  () ; USDA NASS (2022c) SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC; UWM Extension (2014) Pricing, Contracts &amp; Budgets. Cooperative Extension Service, University of Wisconsin-Madison. https://farms.extension.wisc.edu/article-topic/pricing-and-contracts/, Hanna, Mark (2016) Estimating the Field Capacity of Farm Machines. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-24.pdf, Schuler and Frank (1998) A3510 Estimating Agricultural Field Machinery Costs. University of Wisconsin-Extension. https://learningstore.uwex.edu/Assets/pdfs/A3510.pdf, Lattz and Schnitkey (2021b) Machinery Cost Estimates: Field Operations. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/field_operations.pdf</comment>
