          <comment xml:lang="en">biogene carbon content on a dry matter basis; Composition data obtained from Corn Grain Whole, in (http://beefmagazine.com/images/2009%20feed%20table.pdf). First, composition data were refered to 1 kg dry mass. Then, C-contents were calculated considering a C-content/dry mass of 44% in carbohydrates (including fibres), 53% in proteins and 75% in fats. All data from ecoinvent report, n 15a, pg 40, except C-content in protein, that comes from Determination of protein concentration by total organic carbon analysis, Rouwenhorst et al., 1991, J Biochem and Biophys Methods, 22:119-128.</comment>
