      <intermediateExchange id="4b2bd74f-17a1-594f-954e-a5ef3c2c42f5" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007447-40-7" amount="0.00247374783623044" intermediateExchangeId="f9c6e4e7-e45c-423e-b48e-f7e140efb38e" activityLinkId="d24990e6-efed-56f6-9de3-d91a67feae4e">
        <name xml:lang="en">potassium chloride</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">2.47E-3 kg potassium chloride/kg Sweet Corn 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from IFA data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 120.89--26.65--30.6--1.06 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for 2018). Calculated from: average total N application (2018) reported cropped area of specified crop (includes all rotation patterns) and share of fertilisers in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times each fertiliser's K2O to N ratio (IFA), subtracted from the application rate for the necessary nutrient, and multiplied by the mass of the compound over the mass of K2O in the compound. The remaining K2O and S demands are met from a mix of ammonium sulfate, potassium nitrate, potassium chloride, and potassium sulfate, the quantities of which are determined by satisfying the demand without adding any additional excess of any nutrient beyond that resulting from assuming the U.S. average mix of N fertilizers; any S demand remaining is met using elemental sulfur.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2022c) SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
