      <elementaryExchange id="e1a931aa-2876-5fa9-8b22-c4aafd5595da" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="010024-97-2" amount="4.97004413248641E-05" elementaryExchangeId="afd6d670-bbb0-4625-9730-04088a5b035e" formula="N2O">
        <name xml:lang="en">Dinitrogen monoxide</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Direct and indirect N2O emissions from fertilizer and manure use and crop cultivation.  direct emissions: 8.36E-1 kgN2O/ha (4.97E-5 kg N2O/kg Sweet Corn), 4.41E-2 kg N2O/ha from synthetic fertiliser N and 0.E+0 kg N2O/ha from manure N, 5.21E-1kg N2O/ha from crop residues
Emissions from run-off and leaching of N after direct volatilisation of NH3 are calculated using the IPCC National Greenhouse Gas Inventory Guidance (IPCC 2006a, 2019Ra) using Tier 1 and Tier 2 parameters. Direct N2O emissions are calculated using Tier 2 parameters from Table  equation 11.2 of the 2019Refinement to wi of the IPCC National Inventory Guidance, 2019 revision. including contributions from nutrient applications, with the Tier 2 emissions factors for wet climates (Table 11.1, IPCC 2019R) 0.016 kg N2O-N/kg fertiliser N applied (uniform range 0.013--0.019) and 0.006 kgN2O-N/kg manure N applied (uniform range 0.001--0.011) 
Sources: 
IPCC (2006a) 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/pdf/4_Volume4/V4_11_Ch11_N2O&amp;CO2.pdf, https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/
IPCC (2019a)  Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in 2019 Refinement to the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/pdf/4_Volume4/19R_V4_Ch11_Soils_N2O_CO2.pdf https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/index.html, https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2019-refinement-to-the-2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas-inventories/
IPCC (2006b) IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories (Volumes 1, 2, and 4). UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2006gl/index.html
IPCC (2019b) 2019 Refinement to the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories (Volumes 1, 2, and 4). UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2019-refinement-to-the-2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas- inventories/ https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/index.html.       
IPCC (2019c)  Equation 11.1, Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in 2019 Refinement to the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/pdf/4_Volume4/19R_V4_Ch11_Soils_N2O_CO2.pdf https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/index.html, https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2019-refinement-to-the-2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas-inventories/
IPCC (2019d)  Equation 11.2, Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in 2019 Refinement to the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/pdf/4_Volume4/19R_V4_Ch11_Soils_N2O_CO2.pdf https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/index.html, https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2019-refinement-to-the-2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas-inventories/
IPCC (2019e)  Table 11.1(A), Chapter 11: N2O Emissions from Managed Soils, and CO2 Emissions from Lime and Urea Application in 2019 Refinement to the 2006 IPCC Guidelines for National Greenhouse Gas Inventories - Volume 4: Agriculture, Forestry and Other Land Use. UN Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/pdf/4_Volume4/19R_V4_Ch11_Soils_N2O_CO2.pdf https://www.ipcc-nggip.iges.or.jp/public/2019rf/index.html, https://www.ipcc.ch/report/2019-refinement-to-the-2006-ipcc-guidelines-for-national-greenhouse-gas-inventories/</comment>
