        <name xml:lang="en">Glufosinate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Glufosinate emission to agricultural soil (1.113E-01 kg/ha).  Pesticides are assumed to be ultimately 100% emitted to soil across all rotation patterns, based on assumption that all sweet corn acres are treated, and assuming that cultivation is conventional tillage as common practice for weed management (EPA 2022; IPM 2003, IPM 1997).Data reported a quantity of total insecticides/herbicides/fungicides applied in sweet corn is sometimes available even when many of the substances in the category are reported with a “D”. If this total is available, the amount remaining after the sum of substance-specific values is accounted for is divided equally among the substances reported with a “D”. If the sum of available values exceeds or equals the total reported, any remaining “D” substances are treated as zero and omitted.  
