      <elementaryExchange id="693f96c9-30ae-5e44-a26e-e2e27b577c65" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="023713-49-7" amount="2.60773806844953E-05" elementaryExchangeId="541b633c-17a3-4047-bce6-0c0e4fdb7c10" formula="Zn+2">
        <name xml:lang="en">Zinc II</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Emissions of heavy metals to surface water arise from leaching (when drainage is present) and erosion. Emissions are estimated  based on the SALCA-heavy metal model (Freiermuth 2006) following the procedure in the ecoinvent agricultural LCI tool (Faist Emmenegger, Délerce-Mauris and Porté 2018 Models Integrated in Ecoinvent LCI Calculation Tool for Crop Production). The crop system carries a share of heavy metals emissions based on the ratio of cropping additions to total additions (additions to crop system divided by additions to crop system plus depostion from air and present in soils) Sources for heavy metals contents include: Leaching of heavy metals to surface water (Wolfensberger &amp; Dinkel 1997), where drainage is installed ; Average heavy metal contents in crop soils, mg per kg soil, based on data for Switzerland (from Keller &amp; Desaules, 2001). erosion rates are from US NRC National Resources Inventory, 2017. and Drainage on all cropland acres state-wide, including tile drainage (4.2%,) and ditch drainage (5.1%). USDA (2018a) 2017 Census of Agriculture, Volume 1, Chapter 2: State Level Data - Table 41.  Land Use Practices:  2017 and 2012 (live table: https://www.nass.usda.gov/Quick_Stats/CDQT/chapter/2/table/41/state/US). US Department of Agriculture (USDA). https://www.nass.usda.gov/Publications/AgCensus/2017/Full_Report/Volume_1,_Chapter_2_US_State_Level/st99_2_0041_0041.pdf. Fertilizer, manure and pesticide application rates are based on USDA NASS data.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="2.60773806844953E-05" mu="-10.554442259826356" variance="0.09" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0932"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="3" temporalCorrelation="3" geographicalCorrelation="1" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="1"/>
        </uncertainty>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Zinc ion</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Zinc</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Zinc (+2)</synonym>
